n}}\n* {{cite book\n| last = Van der Vat\n| first = Dan\n| title = D-Day: The Greatest Invasion\u2014A People's History\n| year = 2003\n| publisher = Maddison Press\n| isbn = 1-55192-586-9\n| ref = harv\n}}\n* {{cite book\n| last = Weale\n| first = Adrian\n| authorlink = Adrian Weale\n| title = Army of Evil: A History of the SS\n| year = 2012\n| publisher = NAL Caliber (Penguin Group)\n| location = New York; Toronto\n| isbn = 978-0-451-23791-0\n| ref = harv\n}}\n* {{cite book | last = Wegner | first = Bernd | authorlink = Bernd Wegner | title = The Waffen-SS: Organization, Ideology and Function | publisher = Blackwell | year = 1990 | isbn = 0-631-14073-5 | ref = harv }}\n* {{cite book\n| last = Ziemke\n| first = Earl F.\n| authorlink = Earl F. Ziemke\n| title = Stalingrad to Berlin: The German Defeat in the East\n| url = https://archive.org/details/stalingradtoberl00ziem\n| url-access = registration\n| year = 1968\n| publisher = Office of the Chief of Military History \u2013 U.S. Army\n| location = Washington\n| ASIN = B002E5VBSE\n| ref = harv\n}}\n* {{cite book\n| last = Zuccotti\n| first = Susan\n| title = Holocaust Odysseys: The Jews of Saint-Martin-Vesubie and Their Flight through France and Italy\n| year = 2007\n| publisher = Yale University Press\n| location = New Haven\n| isbn = 978-0-300-12294-7\n| ref = harv\n}}\n\n{{refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite book\n| last1 = Glantz\n| first1 = David M.\n| last2 = House\n| first2 = Jonathan M.\n| title = When Titans Clashed: How the Red Army Stopped Hitler\n| year = 1995\n| isbn = 978-0-7006-0717-4\n}}\n\n* {{cite book\n| last=Parrish\n| first=Michael\n| title=The Lesser Terror: Soviet State Security, 1939\u20131953\n| publisher=Praeger Press\n| year=1996\n| isbn=978-0-275-95113-9\n}}\n\n{{SS Divisions}}\n{{SS organizations}}\n{{German Armoured Divisions of World War II}}\n{{Nazi war crimes in Italy}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Subject bar\n| portal1=Military of Germany\n| portal2=Tanks\n| portal3=World War 