{"title_page": "Thoothukudi massacre", "text_new": "{{Infobox civilian attack\n| title       =Thoothukudi Massacare\n| image       = \n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| map         = {{Location map|Tamil Nadu|lat=8.48|long=78.04|caption=}}\n| map_caption = Location of Thoothukudi in Tamil Nadu\n| location    = [[Thoothukudi]], Tamil Nadu, [[India]]\n| target      = Protestors against [[Sterlite Copper]]\n| coordinates = {{Coord|8.784117|78.099142|display=inline,title}}\n| date        = 22 May 2018\n| time        = \n| timezone    = UTC+5:30\n| type        = [[Shooting]]<!-- Don't change without valid reference -->\n| fatalities  = 13<!-- Don't change without valid reference --><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india-sterlite-protest-live-updates-tuticorin-thoothukudi-death-toll-vedanta-copper-plant-443641 |title=Anti-Sterlite protests: 15 dead, 102 injured in Thoothukudi; electricity supply to Sterlite Industries cut off}}</ref>\n| injuries    = 102<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india-sterlite-protest-live-updates-tuticorin-thoothukudi-death-toll-vedanta-copper-plant-443641 |title=Anti-Sterlite protests: 13 dead, 102 injured in Thoothukudi; electricity supply to Sterlite Industries cut off}}</ref>\n| perps       = [[Tamil Nadu Police]] & Paramilitary forces\n| weapons     = [[L1A1 SLR]] [[battle rifle]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.vikatan.com/news/tamilnadu/125778-this-is-the-type-of-rifle-used-in-tuticorin.html |title=\u0ba4\u0bc2\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd 11 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b89\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0ba4\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf \u0b87\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bcd}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/massacre-thoothukudi-intelligence-failure-or-deliberate-assault-81865 |title=The police firing in Thoothukudi: Intelligence failure or deliberate assault?}}</ref>\n| numparts    =\n}}\n\n[[File:Sterlitejpg.jpg|thumb|Protesters in large numbers take out a march against the Sterlite copper plant on May 22, 2018.]]The '''Thoothukudi police firing''' (also known as the '''Thoothukudi Massacre''' or '''Sterlite Protest Firing''') took place on 22 May 2018 in [[Thoothukudi]], [[Tamil Nadu]], India, when [[Tamil Nadu Police]] officers fired into a crowd of 20,000 people<ref name=\"financialexpress\" /> protesting against the [[Sterlite Copper]] factory which was allegedly causing environmental pollution.<ref name=\"financialexpress\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/india-news/sterlite-protest-in-tuticorin-9-killed-in-tamil-nadu-top-developments-history-reasons-behind-violence/1177652/|title=Reasons behind Killings|last=|first=|date=|work=The Financial Express|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nSporadic protests have occurred in [[Thoothukudi]], a district in the Indian state of [[Tamil Nadu]] since 1999, directed against the Sterlite Copper smelting factory. The factory is owned by [[Vedanta Limited]], a subsidiary of [[Vedanta Resources]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailyo.in/variety/sterlite-protests-sulphur-dioxide-vedanta-tamil-nadu/story/1/23101.html|title=Why hundreds of Tamils won't quit protests against Vedanta's Sterlite|website=www.dailyo.in|access-date=2018-05-28}}</ref> Protestors oppose soil, water and air contamination caused by the factory<ref>http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/sterlite-s-pollution-problem-113041801267_1.html</ref>. An epidemiological study carried out by [[Tirunelveli Medical College]] in 2006\u201307 had found increased prevalence of respiratory diseases and ear, nose and throat (ENT) morbidity in the area within a radius of 5&nbsp;km of the factory. Their report blamed this on air pollution caused by the industry, thermal power plants and automobiles such as trucks and heavy vehicles plying in the area.<ref>{{cite book | last = Elango  | first = S. | title = Health status and Epidemiological study around 5&nbsp;km radius of Sterlite Industries (India) Limited, Thoothukudi | publisher = Tirunelveli Medical College | date = Oct 2008 | location = Tirunelveli | pages = 106 | language = English | url = https://poromboke.files.wordpress.com/2018/03/health-report-sterlite_edited.pdf}}</ref>\n\nIron content in the [[groundwater]] surrounding the plant has been found to be 17\u201320 times the allowed limit, causing additional health problems for the population already experiencing higher than average incidence of respiratory diseases.<ref name=newsminute>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/sterlite-here-s-proof-how-copper-plant-impacts-health-thoothukudi-people-78772|title=Sterlite \u2013 here's the proof: How the copper plant impacts health of Thoothukudi people|date=2018-04-01|work=The News Minute|access-date=2018-05-22}}</ref> The plant is less than 15 km from the [[Gulf of Mannar Biosphere Reserve]]. More than 2.5 lakh (250,000) people live in the vicinity of the plant.\n\nThe Sterlite factory made headlines in 2013 due to an alleged gas leak which was not proven in court.<ref name=financialexpress /> The plant was blamed for health issues observed in the area related to gas leakage. Following the alleged gas leak in March 2013, the then chief minister, the late [[J. Jayalalithaa]], ordered its closure. The company appealed to the [[National Green Tribunal Act|National Green Tribunal]], which overturned the government order. The state moved the [[Supreme Court of India|Supreme Court]] against it. The Supreme Court ordered the company to pay a 100-crore fine in 2015 and the factory was allowed to open after being shutdown by the pollution regulator<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/sc-slaps-rs-100-cr-penalty-on-sterlite-for-pollution/article4572805.ece|title=SC slaps Rs. 100 cr. penalty on Sterlite for pollution|last=Venkatesan|first=J.|date=2013-04-02|work=The Hindu|access-date=2018-05-28|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref>. The plant again closed on March 27 of 2018, with the company citing a 15-day maintenance process<ref name=\"financialexpress\" />.\n\nAfter Sterlite announced its plans to expand the plant, people around Kumarettipuram village protested for more than 100 days<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vikatan.com/news/tamilnadu/120896-after-kumarettiyapuram-pandarampatti-village-people-joins-sterlite-protest-in-thoothukudi.html|title=\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bc6\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bb8\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b9f\u0bcd \u0b86\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0bae\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bae\u0bcd|date=2018-04-01|work=Vikatan|access-date=2018-05-22|language=ta}}</ref>. A major protest had been conducted peacefully till March 29, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ucanews.com/news/catholics-among-11-dead-as-police-fire-on-india-protest/82392|title=Catholics among 11 dead as police fire on India protest|website=ucanews.com|language=en|access-date=2019-04-30}}</ref>\n\n== Protests in 2018 ==\nProtests against the plant began peacefully on 12th February 2018 when Sterlite announced its expansion programme<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rediff.com/business/special/sterlite-protest-villagers-versus-anil-agarwal/20180426.htm|title=Anti-Sterlite Protests: Who Is Behind The Tuticorin Turmoil?|last=|first=|date=|website=swarajyamag.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>. Villagers from the neighbouring village of Kumarettipuram protested by staging a fast. Police arrested over 250 people on that day including several activists as permission for the protests was not obtained from the authorities.  This did not deter the protestors as people from other villages also started joining in.\n\nThe protests were joined by traders of Thoothukudi city central trade association in Thoothukudi on 24th March following calls for a bandh (shutdown) by environmental activist Mr. M Krishnamoorthi<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/nation/current-affairs/200318/thoothukudi-foreign-hand-behind-anti-sterlite-stir.html|title=Thoothukudi: \u2018Foreign hand\u2019 behind anti-Sterlite stir|date=2018-03-20|website=Deccan Chronicle|language=en|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>. Popular Tamil actor Kamal Hasan extended his support to the protests on Twitter and participated in the protests on 1st April 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/maiamofficial/status/980346820416032768|title=\u0b87\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0baf \u0b8e\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd, \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc8\u0baf \u0bb5\u0bb3\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd...\n\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0ba8\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bc7!!\n\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0baf\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bc7!!\n#MNMforThoothukudi #NammavarAgainstSterlitepic.twitter.com/vPz02YlpKw|last=\u0bae\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baf\u0bae\u0bcd|first=Makkal Needhi Maiam {{!}} \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bbf|date=2018-04-01|website=@maiamofficial|language=ta|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>. On the same day, Thirumurugan Gandhi, a Tamil human rights activist also joined the protest. Later popular Christian evangelist Mohan C Lazarus also lent his voice to the protests and participated in it for a day<ref>{{Citation|title=Tuticorin Sterlite injustice ~\u0b9a\u0b95\u0bcb.\u0bae\u0bcb\u0b95\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bbf. \u0bb2\u0bbe\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bb8\u0bcd #Sterlite #Tuticorin|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r-gg3wt04G0|language=en|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>.\n\nOn 20th May, Ms. Fatima Babu (environmental activist), Mr. P Vinayagamoorthi (president of Thoothukudi city central trade association) and 21 other people among the protestors were called by the district administration for a peace meeting. Following the peace meeting, both Mr. P Vinayagamoorthi and Ms. Fatima Babu agreed to shift the venue of the protests from the collectorate (district collector's office) area to SAV ground and to convert the protest to a 'protest to gather attention for a cause'. [It is unclear when protests began to be held in front of the collectorate]\n\nFollowing the acceptance of decisions taken in the peace meeting, Ms. Fatima Babu was expelled from the agitation committee. On 22nd May, two groups of people protested separately. One group of people were protesting at SAV ground and the other was marching towards the collectorate. When those protesting at SAV ground saw the other group moving towards the collectorate, the former too joined the latter. Barricades put up by police were broken through using cows. Police resorted to lathi-charge and fired tear gas shells at the crowd after arguments with the protestors who wanted to stage a sit-in. There were about 2000 police personnel and a crowd of over 20,000 protestors. The district administration neglected intelligence reports of mass mobilization of over 18,000 people in the district<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil-nadu/2018/may/27/anti-sterlite-in-thoothukudi-heart-of-darkness-1819970.html|title=Anti-Sterlite in Thoothukudi: Heart of darkness|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>. \n\n== Allegations of involvement of anti-social groups, revolutionary groups and 'foreign hand' ==\nMany claim the involvement of separatist and revolutionary groups like Makkal Athikaram (translation: People's power) Puthiya Jananayagam (translation: New Democracy), and Revolutionary Student and Youth Federation in the protests<ref name=\":1\" />. Videos of \"anti-social elements\" setting fire to residential flats of Sterlite employees and burning vehicles were circulated on WhatsApp. Some of the protestors also engaged in burning tyres, vehicles near the collectorate and setting fire to Sterlite employees' flats<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://scroll.in/article/880329/view-from-the-other-side-sterlite-workers-attacked-by-thoothukudi-protestors-recall-the-terror|title=View from the other side: Sterlite workers attacked by Thoothukudi protestors recall the terror|last=Govindarajan|first=Vinita|website=Scroll.in|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>. Foil Vedanta, an \"independent grassroots solidarity organisation\" that aims to have Vedanta, Sterlite Corporation's parent company de-listed from London's stock market also lent its hand to the protests<ref name=\":0\" />. Allegations of involvement of foreign Christian missionaries in funding of the protests were also made<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vaanaram.in/missionaries_links_in_sterlite_protests/|title=Role of Christian missionaries in Sterlite protests|last=teamvaanaram|date=2018-12-30|website=\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>. Days after the protests turned violent, people from the village of Madathur alleged that outfits like Makkal Adhigaram \"changed their hearts\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/india/anti-sterlite-protests-tuticorin-villagers-accuse-left-outfit-of-inciting-violence-5247129/|title=Anti-Sterlite protests: Tuticorin villagers accuse Left outfit of inciting violence|date=2018-07-06|website=The Indian Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>.\n\n==Firing==\n\nOn May 22, 2018, over 20,000 people began to march to the district collector's office to submit a petition when section 144 had been imposed. Section 144 of the Indian Penal Code (IPC) imposes curfew like restrictions in the area. A gathering of 5 or more people is illegal when it is in effect but an unofficial release said 20,000 people took out a procession towards the district collectorate and the copper plant<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://india.ucanews.com/news/tuticorin-police-massacre-leaves-11-dead-priest-in-hospital/37364/daily|title=Tuticorin police massacre leaves 11 dead, christian priest Fr.Rev.Leo jayaseelan in hospital who was responsible for the little children and housewives from the church to larcilate the protests apart from the Urban naxals like \"Makkal Athigaram\"{{!}} UCAN India|website=india.ucanews.com|access-date=2018-05-28}}</ref>. Protestors were successful in entering the premises of the collectorate. The police started shooting against the protesters, \"without any formal warning\" after tear gas and lathi-charge proved ineffective.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/6-km-stir-ended-bloodshed-671436.html|title=A 6-km stir that ended in bloodshed|date=2018-05-23|access-date=2018-05-23|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/police-targeted-protesters-shot-head-victims-families-671547.html|title=Police targeted the protesters; shot at head|date=2018-05-24|access-date=2018-05-24|language=en}}</ref>  Police intentionally shot at the heads of the protesters<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://zeenews.india.com/tamil-nadu/tamil-nadu-police-fired-from-assault-rifles-on-anti-sterlite-protesters-heard-saying-at-least-one-should-die-2110643.html|title=Tamil Nadu Police fired from assault rifles on anti-Sterlite protesters, heard saying at least one should die{{!}} Zee News India|website=zeenews.india.com|access-date=2018-06-02}}</ref> 13 protesters were killed <ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/as-tuticorin-weeps-for-13-felled-in-police-firing-a-quite-rage-persists/articleshow/64334132.cms</ref> including a 17-year old school student, and dozens were injured.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/she-wanted-be-lawyer-her-dreams-lie-box-thoothukudi-teen-victim-s-kin-81854|title=She wanted to be a lawyer, her dreams lie in a box|date=2018-05-24|access-date=2018-05-24|language=en}}</ref><ref name=fivedays /> \n\nFIRs filed in local police stations claimed that the order to shoot was issued by officers in the rank of deputy tahsildars. Some people pointed out that only Collectors have the authority to issue shooting orders.<ref name=\"TH20180529-1\">{{cite news | last = Pon Vasanth | first = B. A | title = Three officers in the rank of deputy tahsildar issued firing orders in Thoothukudi, say FIRs | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Madurai | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 29 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/3-deputy-tahsildars-issued-firing-orders-say-firs/article24017934.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe Tamil Nadu government ordered a shutdown of Internet in the entire districts of Tuticorin, Tirunelveli and Kanyakumari for five days after the firing.<ref name=\"fivedays\">{{cite web |title=Sterlite protest: Tamil Nadu orders internet suspension for five days in three southern districts |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil-nadu/2018/may/23/sterlite-protest-tamil-nadu-orders-internet-suspension-for-five-days-in-three-southern-districts-1818574.html |website=New Indian Express |accessdate=9 July 2018 |date=23 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Reactions==\n\n* [[Thirumurugan Gandhi]], the coordinator of [[May 17 Movement]], took the issue to the 38th session of the [[United Nations Human Rights Council]], Geneva in July 2018. On 9 August 2018, Thirumurugan Gandhi was detained by immigration authorities at Bangalore Airport on his return to India and charged under Section 124 A (sedition), 153 A (1) and 153 (b) of IPC for speaking about the Thoothukudi firings at the UNHRC. Court, later, refused to remand him under judicial custody as it found the charges are baseless.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/court-refuses-detain-activist-thirumurugan-gandhi-86351|title=Court refuses to detain activist Thirumurugan Gandhi|date=2018-08-10|work=The News Minute|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/2018/aug/10/thirumurugan-gandhi-held-in-bengaluru-for-un-speech-on-police-firing-in-thoothukudi-1855732.html|title=Thirumurugan Gandhi held in Bengaluru for UN speech on police firing in Thoothukudi|work=The New Indian Express|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref>\n* [[Indian National Congress]] party president [[Rahul Gandhi]] described it as \"[[state-sponsored terrorism]]\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://zeenews.india.com/india/anti-sterlite-protest-gunning-down-9-people-by-police-in-tamil-nadu-is-state-sponsored-terrorism-says-rahul-gandhi-2110523.html?src=fb|title=Anti-Sterlite protest: Gunning down 9 people by police in Tamil Nadu is state-sponsored terrorism, says Rahul Gandhi|date=2018-05-22|work=Zee News|access-date=2018-05-22|language=en}}</ref> \n*[[Seeman (politician)|Seeman]] condemned the firing, and his political party held a rally in Tirunelveli condemning the shooting.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tamil.oneindia.com/news/tamilnadu/seeman-condemns-the-gun-firing-at-thoothukudi-protest/articlecontent-pf308746-320470.html|title=Naam Thamizhar Katchi leader Seeman condemns gun firing at Thoothukudi|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=2018-05-31}}</ref>\n* [[Kamal Haasan]] was one of the first political leaders to arrive to Tuticorin to see the injured in the hospital, after the shootings.\n* [[Vaiko]] and [[M.K.Stalin]] demanded investigations into the shootings.<ref>http://indianexpress.com/article/india/mass-murder-of-innocent-people-dmks-stalin-questions-order-to-fire-at-anti-sterlite-protesters-5187874/</ref>\n* [[National Human Rights Commission of India]] demanded investigation into the killings.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2018/05/indian-police-accused-killing-11-protesters-180523134721427.html |title=Indian police accused of killing at least 11 protesters}}</ref> It asked its Director General (Investigation) to send a team headed by an [[Superintendent of Police|SP]] to visit the spot and conduct an inquiry.<ref name=\"TH20180530-1\" />\n* Tamils and [[Tamil diaspora]] across the world including [[United States]], [[Canada]], [[Europe]], [[Malaysia]], [[Sri Lanka]] and [[Australia]] held protests against the killing.\n* In support of the protests The UK's Opposition, Labour Party, has called for Vedanta to be delisted from the London Stock Exchange. [[John McDonnell]], the UK's Shadow Chancellor, said removing Vedanta Resources from the London financial markets would prevent reputational damage from the \"rogue\" company which has been operating \"illegal\" mining concerns for years. \"After the firing on the protestors this week, regulators must now take action. Vedanta must be immediately delisted from the London Stock Exchange to remove its cloak of respectability, restore confidence in the governance of the Stock Exchange, and prevent further reputational damage to London's financial markets from this rogue corporation,\" McDonnell said in a statement .<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/uk-opposition-wants-vedanta-delisted-from-london-stock-exchange/articleshow/64331300.cms |title=UK Opposition wants Vedanta delisted on London Stock Exchange}}</ref>\n* Actor [[Rajinikanth]] said \"anti-social elements had infiltrated the crowd causing violence and should have been dealt with an iron hand\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wionews.com/india-news/rajinikanth-issued-summons-over-anti-social-elements-remark-on-tuticorin-violence-firing-278579|title=Rajinikanth issued summons over \u2018anti-social elements\u2019 remark on Tuticorin violence, firing|website=WION|language=en|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref> and also stated that Tamil Nadu would become a graveyard if the people of the state keep protesting against everything<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-44313804|title=Rajinikanth: Anger after actor justifies deadly police firing|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/rajinikanth-blames-anti-social-elements-for-sterlite-protest201805302030500001/ |title=Rajinikanth blames anti-social elements for Sterlite protest}}</ref>. Also, his angry reaction on media was criticized and his statements were brought negative impact on social media.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-superstar-rajinikanth-apologises-for-losing-cool-at-media-interaction-2621031 |title=Superstar Rajinikanth apologises for losing cool at media interaction |access-date=3 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/rajinikanth-s-speech-earns-him-negative-image-on-social-media-news-tamil-sf5jD6fcigihb.html|title=Rajinikanth's speech earns him negative image on social media?|access-date=3 June 2018}}</ref> Following his controversial statements regarding the Thoothukudi shooting scandal, the Tamil activist groups in [[Norway]] and [[Switzerland]] banned the release of Rajinikanth's [[Kaala (2018 film)|''Kaala'']] in Norway and Switzerland by the scheduled world wide release date as of 7 June.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tamil.news18.com/news/entertainment/after-norway-kaala-ban-in-swiss-too-24491.html|title=\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bbe \u0baa\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0b9f \u0bae\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u2013 News18 Tamil|website=News18 Tamil|access-date=2018-06-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tamil.samayam.com/tamil-cinema/movie-news/rajinikanth-kaala-movie-banned-in-switzerland-and-norway/articleshow/64428551.cms|title=\u0bb0\u0b9c\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc7, \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bbe \u0baa\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc8 - Samayam Tamil|date=2018-06-02|work=[[Samayam Tamil]]|access-date=2018-06-03|language=ta}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/foreign-nations-ban-rajinis-kaala-tamil-news-214931|title=Foreign nations ban Rajini's 'Kaala'? - Tamil Movie News \u2013 IndiaGlitz.com|work=IndiaGlitz.com|access-date=2018-06-03}}</ref> The Tamil diaspora groups in Norway and Switzerland announced that they would not release the films of actors in the future who deliberately hurt the feelings and attitudes of Tamil people following the comments from Rajinikanth on Tamils.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tamilnews.com/2018/06/01/switzerland-ban-super-star-movie-following-norway/|title=\u0ba8\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0bb8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd '\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bbe' \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc8??|last=S|first=Ashwiniya|date=2018-06-01|work=TAMIL NEWS|access-date=2018-06-03|language=en-US}}</ref> However, the ban was later on lifted and the film was released with a week delay resp. a day before the scheduled worldwide release in Switzerland and Norway, respectively.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.topkino.ch/pdf/Programm24.pdf|title=Wochenprogramm|date=2018-06-11|work=Top Kino|access-date=2018-06-19|language=de-CH|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619085834/http://www.topkino.ch/pdf/Programm24.pdf|archivedate=2018-06-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.filmweb.no/film/article1361077.ece|title=Kaala (Tamil)|date=2018-06-01|work=Filmweb|access-date=2018-06-19|language=no-NO|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619090401/https://www.filmweb.no/film/article1361077.ece|archivedate=2018-06-19}}</ref>  The actor was also summoned to appear before the one man commission probing the incident on 25th February. However, the actor cited professional engagements and disturbance caused to the public if a star of his stature arrives at the court to decline appearing before the commission. He has since filed an affidavit with the commission answering the questions posed by them<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/south/thoothukudi-sterlite-copper-plant-probe-rajinikanth-gets-exemption-from-appearance-808094.html|title=Thoothukudi Sterlite Copper plant probe: Rajinikanth gets exemption from appearance|date=2020-02-25|website=Deccan Herald|language=en|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>.\n\nA video released by the environmental activist a few days before he went missing from a train while traveling to Madurai from Chennai, S. Mugilan says the \"shooting was well planned\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/rights/environmental-activist-missing-thoothukudi-massacre-police|title=Activist Goes Missing Hours After Incriminating Top Cops in Thoothukudi Massacre|website=The Wire|access-date=2019-03-20}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=TuNo|title=Arsonists - Sterlite - The Hidden Truth - \u0b95\u0bca\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd? \u0bb8\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b9f\u0bcd - \u0bae\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0b89\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd|date=2019-02-08|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SlukGKrzYLc|access-date=2019-03-20}}</ref>\n\n== Government response ==\nOn 28 May 2018, the Sterlite factory was sealed by an order of the Tamil Nadu Environmental pollutions and Forests Department.<ref name=\"TH20180528-1\">{{cite news | last = Rohit | first = T. K. | title = Sterlite Copper to be permanently closed, says Tamil Nadu government | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Chennai | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 28 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/sterlite-copper-to-be-permanently-closed-says-tamil-nadu-government/article24014605.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref> The next day, Tamil Nadu's State Industries Promotion Corporation (SIPCOT) announced that it would take back 342.22 acres of land that it had given for expansion of the facility.<ref name=\"TH20180530-1\">{{cite news | title = T.N. to take back land allotted to Sterlite | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Chennai / New Delhi | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 30 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/tn-to-take-back-land-allotted-to-sterlite/article24029865.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref> Many political leaders  including [[M.K.Stalin]], [[Seeman (politician)|Seeman]] and [[Anbumani Ramadoss]] criticised the sealing order, saying that it would not stand up to legal scrutiny since the government had given no reason for shutting down the factory<ref name=\"TH20180530-2\">{{cite news | title = G.O. won't stand up to legal scrutiny: Stalin | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Chennai | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 30 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/go-wont-stand-up-to-legal-scrutiny-stalin/article24027956.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"TH20180530-3\">{{cite news | title = G.O. to close Sterlite plant inadequate | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Chennai | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 30 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/go-to-close-sterlite-plant-inadequate/article24030059.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref>.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Manjolai Labourers massacre]]\n* [[2018 Tamil Nadu protests for Kaveri water sharing]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Pollution in India]]\n[[Category:Police brutality in India]]\n[[Category:2018 in Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:2018 murders in Asia]]\n[[Category:May 2018 crimes in Asia|Thoothukudi_firing]]\n[[Category:Thoothukudi]]\n[[Category:Protests in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{cleanup|article|reason=English grammar & spelling|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox civilian attack\n| title       =Thoothukudi Massacare\n| image       = \n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| map         = {{Location map|Tamil Nadu|lat=8.48|long=78.04|caption=}}\n| map_caption = Location of Thoothukudi in Tamil Nadu\n| location    = [[Thoothukudi]], Tamil Nadu, [[India]]\n| target      = Protestors against [[Sterlite Copper]]\n| coordinates = {{Coord|8.784117|78.099142|display=inline,title}}\n| date        = 22 May 2018\n| time        = \n| timezone    = UTC+5:30\n| type        = [[Shooting]]<!-- Don't change without valid reference -->\n| fatalities  = 13<!-- Don't change without valid reference --><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india-sterlite-protest-live-updates-tuticorin-thoothukudi-death-toll-vedanta-copper-plant-443641 |title=Anti-Sterlite protests: 15 dead, 102 injured in Thoothukudi; electricity supply to Sterlite Industries cut off}}</ref>\n| injuries    = 102<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india-sterlite-protest-live-updates-tuticorin-thoothukudi-death-toll-vedanta-copper-plant-443641 |title=Anti-Sterlite protests: 13 dead, 102 injured in Thoothukudi; electricity supply to Sterlite Industries cut off}}</ref>\n| perps       = [[Tamil Nadu Police]] & Paramilitary forces\n| weapons     = [[L1A1 SLR]] [[battle rifle]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.vikatan.com/news/tamilnadu/125778-this-is-the-type-of-rifle-used-in-tuticorin.html |title=\u0ba4\u0bc2\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd 11 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b89\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0ba4\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf \u0b87\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bcd}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/massacre-thoothukudi-intelligence-failure-or-deliberate-assault-81865 |title=The police firing in Thoothukudi: Intelligence failure or deliberate assault?}}</ref>\n| numparts    =\n}}\n\n[[File:Sterlitejpg.jpg|thumb|Protesters in large numbers take out a march against the Sterlite copper plant on May 22, 2018.]]The '''Thoothukudi police firing''' (also known as the '''Thoothukudi Massacre''' or '''Sterlite Protest Firing''') took place on 22 May 2018 in [[Thoothukudi]], [[Tamil Nadu]], India, when [[Tamil Nadu Police]] officers fired into a crowd of 20,000 people<ref name=\"financialexpress\" /> protesting against the [[Sterlite Copper]] factory which was allegedly causing environmental pollution.<ref name=\"financialexpress\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/india-news/sterlite-protest-in-tuticorin-9-killed-in-tamil-nadu-top-developments-history-reasons-behind-violence/1177652/|title=Reasons behind Killings|last=|first=|date=|work=The Financial Express|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nSporadic protests have occurred in [[Thoothukudi]], a district in the Indian state of [[Tamil Nadu]] since 1999, directed against the Sterlite Copper smelting factory. The factory is owned by [[Vedanta Limited]], a subsidiary of [[Vedanta Resources]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailyo.in/variety/sterlite-protests-sulphur-dioxide-vedanta-tamil-nadu/story/1/23101.html|title=Why hundreds of Tamils won't quit protests against Vedanta's Sterlite|website=www.dailyo.in|access-date=2018-05-28}}</ref> Protestors oppose soil, water and air contamination caused by the factory<ref>http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/sterlite-s-pollution-problem-113041801267_1.html</ref>. An epidemiological study carried out by [[Tirunelveli Medical College]] in 2006\u201307 had found increased prevalence of respiratory diseases and ear, nose and throat (ENT) morbidity in the area within a radius of 5&nbsp;km of the factory. Their report blamed this on air pollution caused by the industry, thermal power plants and automobiles such as trucks and heavy vehicles plying in the area.<ref>{{cite book | last = Elango  | first = S. | title = Health status and Epidemiological study around 5&nbsp;km radius of Sterlite Industries (India) Limited, Thoothukudi | publisher = Tirunelveli Medical College | date = Oct 2008 | location = Tirunelveli | pages = 106 | language = English | url = https://poromboke.files.wordpress.com/2018/03/health-report-sterlite_edited.pdf}}</ref>\n\nIron content in the [[groundwater]] surrounding the plant has been found to be 17\u201320 times the allowed limit, causing additional health problems for the population already experiencing higher than average incidence of respiratory diseases.<ref name=newsminute>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/sterlite-here-s-proof-how-copper-plant-impacts-health-thoothukudi-people-78772|title=Sterlite \u2013 here's the proof: How the copper plant impacts health of Thoothukudi people|date=2018-04-01|work=The News Minute|access-date=2018-05-22}}</ref> The plant is less than 15 km from the [[Gulf of Mannar Biosphere Reserve]]. More than 2.5 lakh (250,000) people live in the vicinity of the plant.\n\nThe Sterlite factory made headlines in 2013 due to an alleged gas leak which was not proven in court.<ref name=financialexpress /> The plant was blamed for health issues observed in the area related to gas leakage. Following the alleged gas leak in March 2013, the then chief minister, the late [[J. Jayalalithaa]], ordered its closure. The company appealed to the [[National Green Tribunal Act|National Green Tribunal]], which overturned the government order. The state moved the [[Supreme Court of India|Supreme Court]] against it. The Supreme Court ordered the company to pay a 100-crore fine in 2015 and the factory was allowed to open after being shutdown by the pollution regulator<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/sc-slaps-rs-100-cr-penalty-on-sterlite-for-pollution/article4572805.ece|title=SC slaps Rs. 100 cr. penalty on Sterlite for pollution|last=Venkatesan|first=J.|date=2013-04-02|work=The Hindu|access-date=2018-05-28|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref>. The plant again closed on March 27 of 2018, with the company citing a 15-day maintenance process<ref name=\"financialexpress\" />.\n\nAfter Sterlite announced its plans to expand the plant, people around Kumarettipuram village protested for more than 100 days<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vikatan.com/news/tamilnadu/120896-after-kumarettiyapuram-pandarampatti-village-people-joins-sterlite-protest-in-thoothukudi.html|title=\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bc6\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bb8\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b9f\u0bcd \u0b86\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0bae\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bae\u0bcd|date=2018-04-01|work=Vikatan|access-date=2018-05-22|language=ta}}</ref>. A major protest had been conducted peacefully till March 29, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ucanews.com/news/catholics-among-11-dead-as-police-fire-on-india-protest/82392|title=Catholics among 11 dead as police fire on India protest|website=ucanews.com|language=en|access-date=2019-04-30}}</ref>\n\n== Protests in 2018 ==\nProtests against the plant began peacefully on 12th February 2018 when Sterlite announced its expansion programme<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rediff.com/business/special/sterlite-protest-villagers-versus-anil-agarwal/20180426.htm|title=Anti-Sterlite Protests: Who Is Behind The Tuticorin Turmoil?|last=|first=|date=|website=swarajyamag.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>. Villagers from the neighbouring village of Kumarettipuram protested by staging a fast. Police arrested over 250 people on that day including several activists as permission for the protests was not obtained from the authorities.  This did not deter the protestors as people from other villages also started joining in.\n\nThe protests were joined by traders of Thoothukudi city central trade association in Thoothukudi on 24th March following calls for a bandh (shutdown) by environmental activist Mr. M Krishnamoorthi<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/nation/current-affairs/200318/thoothukudi-foreign-hand-behind-anti-sterlite-stir.html|title=Thoothukudi: \u2018Foreign hand\u2019 behind anti-Sterlite stir|date=2018-03-20|website=Deccan Chronicle|language=en|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>. Popular Tamil actor Kamal Hasan extended his support to the protests on Twitter and participated in the protests on 1st April 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/maiamofficial/status/980346820416032768|title=\u0b87\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0baf \u0b8e\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd, \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc8\u0baf \u0bb5\u0bb3\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd...\n\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0ba8\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bc7!!\n\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0baf\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bc7!!\n#MNMforThoothukudi #NammavarAgainstSterlitepic.twitter.com/vPz02YlpKw|last=\u0bae\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baf\u0bae\u0bcd|first=Makkal Needhi Maiam {{!}} \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bbf|date=2018-04-01|website=@maiamofficial|language=ta|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>. On the same day, Thirumurugan Gandhi, a Tamil human rights activist also joined the protest. Later popular Christian evangelist Mohan C Lazarus also lent his voice to the protests and participated in it for a day<ref>{{Citation|title=Tuticorin Sterlite injustice ~\u0b9a\u0b95\u0bcb.\u0bae\u0bcb\u0b95\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bbf. \u0bb2\u0bbe\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bb8\u0bcd #Sterlite #Tuticorin|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r-gg3wt04G0|language=en|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>.\n\nOn 20th May, Ms. Fatima Babu (environmental activist), Mr. P Vinayagamoorthi (president of Thoothukudi city central trade association) and 21 other people among the protestors were called by the district administration for a peace meeting. Following the peace meeting, both Mr. P Vinayagamoorthi and Ms. Fatima Babu agreed to shift the venue of the protests from the collectorate (district collector's office) area to SAV ground and to convert the protest to a 'protest to gather attention for a cause'. [It is unclear when protests began to be held in front of the collectorate]\n\nFollowing the acceptance of decisions taken in the peace meeting, Ms. Fatima Babu was expelled from the agitation committee. On 22nd May, two groups of people protested separately. One group of people were protesting at SAV ground and the other was marching towards the collectorate. When those protesting at SAV ground saw the other group moving towards the collectorate, the former too joined the latter. Barricades put up by police were broken through using cows. Police resorted to lathi-charge and fired tear gas shells at the crowd after arguments with the protestors who wanted to stage a sit-in. There were about 2000 police personnel and a crowd of over 20,000 protestors. The district administration neglected intelligence reports of mass mobilization of over 18,000 people in the district<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil-nadu/2018/may/27/anti-sterlite-in-thoothukudi-heart-of-darkness-1819970.html|title=Anti-Sterlite in Thoothukudi: Heart of darkness|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>. \n\n== Allegations of involvement of anti-social groups, revolutionary groups and 'foreign hand' ==\nMany claim the involvement of separatist and revolutionary groups like Makkal Athikaram (translation: People's power) Puthiya Jananayagam (translation: New Democracy), and Revolutionary Student and Youth Federation in the protests<ref name=\":1\" />. Videos of \"anti-social elements\" setting fire to residential flats of Sterlite employees and burning vehicles were circulated on WhatsApp. Some of the protestors also engaged in burning tyres, vehicles near the collectorate and setting fire to Sterlite employees' flats<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://scroll.in/article/880329/view-from-the-other-side-sterlite-workers-attacked-by-thoothukudi-protestors-recall-the-terror|title=View from the other side: Sterlite workers attacked by Thoothukudi protestors recall the terror|last=Govindarajan|first=Vinita|website=Scroll.in|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>. Foil Vedanta, an \"independent grassroots solidarity organisation\" that aims to have Vedanta, Sterlite Corporation's parent company de-listed from London's stock market also lent its hand to the protests<ref name=\":0\" />. Allegations of involvement of foreign Christian missionaries in funding of the protests were also made<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vaanaram.in/missionaries_links_in_sterlite_protests/|title=Role of Christian missionaries in Sterlite protests|last=teamvaanaram|date=2018-12-30|website=\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>. Days after the protests turned violent, people from the village of Madathur alleged that outfits like Makkal Adhigaram \"changed their hearts\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/india/anti-sterlite-protests-tuticorin-villagers-accuse-left-outfit-of-inciting-violence-5247129/|title=Anti-Sterlite protests: Tuticorin villagers accuse Left outfit of inciting violence|date=2018-07-06|website=The Indian Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>.\n\n==Firing==\n\nOn May 22, 2018, over 20,000 people began to march to the district collector's office to submit a petition when section 144 had been imposed. Section 144 of the Indian Penal Code (IPC) imposes curfew like restrictions in the area. A gathering of 5 or more people is illegal when it is in effect but an unofficial release said 20,000 people took out a procession towards the district collectorate and the copper plant<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://india.ucanews.com/news/tuticorin-police-massacre-leaves-11-dead-priest-in-hospital/37364/daily|title=Tuticorin police massacre leaves 11 dead, christian priest Fr.Rev.Leo jayaseelan in hospital who was responsible for the little children and housewives from the church to larcilate the protests apart from the Urban naxals like \"Makkal Athigaram\"{{!}} UCAN India|website=india.ucanews.com|access-date=2018-05-28}}</ref>. Protestors were successful in entering the premises of the collectorate. The police started shooting against the protesters, \"without any formal warning\" after tear gas and lathi-charge proved ineffective.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/6-km-stir-ended-bloodshed-671436.html|title=A 6-km stir that ended in bloodshed|date=2018-05-23|access-date=2018-05-23|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/police-targeted-protesters-shot-head-victims-families-671547.html|title=Police targeted the protesters; shot at head|date=2018-05-24|access-date=2018-05-24|language=en}}</ref>  Police intentionally shot at the heads of the protesters<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://zeenews.india.com/tamil-nadu/tamil-nadu-police-fired-from-assault-rifles-on-anti-sterlite-protesters-heard-saying-at-least-one-should-die-2110643.html|title=Tamil Nadu Police fired from assault rifles on anti-Sterlite protesters, heard saying at least one should die{{!}} Zee News India|website=zeenews.india.com|access-date=2018-06-02}}</ref> 13 protesters were killed <ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/as-tuticorin-weeps-for-13-felled-in-police-firing-a-quite-rage-persists/articleshow/64334132.cms</ref> including a 17-year old school student, and dozens were injured.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/she-wanted-be-lawyer-her-dreams-lie-box-thoothukudi-teen-victim-s-kin-81854|title=She wanted to be a lawyer, her dreams lie in a box|date=2018-05-24|access-date=2018-05-24|language=en}}</ref><ref name=fivedays /> \n\nFIRs filed in local police stations claimed that the order to shoot was issued by officers in the rank of deputy tahsildars. Some people pointed out that only Collectors have the authority to issue shooting orders.<ref name=\"TH20180529-1\">{{cite news | last = Pon Vasanth | first = B. A | title = Three officers in the rank of deputy tahsildar issued firing orders in Thoothukudi, say FIRs | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Madurai | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 29 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/3-deputy-tahsildars-issued-firing-orders-say-firs/article24017934.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe Tamil Nadu government ordered a shutdown of Internet in the entire districts of Tuticorin, Tirunelveli and Kanyakumari for five days after the firing.<ref name=\"fivedays\">{{cite web |title=Sterlite protest: Tamil Nadu orders internet suspension for five days in three southern districts |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil-nadu/2018/may/23/sterlite-protest-tamil-nadu-orders-internet-suspension-for-five-days-in-three-southern-districts-1818574.html |website=New Indian Express |accessdate=9 July 2018 |date=23 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Reactions==\n\n* [[Thirumurugan Gandhi]], the coordinator of [[May 17 Movement]], took the issue to the 38th session of the [[United Nations Human Rights Council]], Geneva in July 2018. On 9 August 2018, Thirumurugan Gandhi was detained by immigration authorities at Bangalore Airport on his return to India and charged under Section 124 A (sedition), 153 A (1) and 153 (b) of IPC for speaking about the Thoothukudi firings at the UNHRC. Court, later, refused to remand him under judicial custody as it found the charges are baseless.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/court-refuses-detain-activist-thirumurugan-gandhi-86351|title=Court refuses to detain activist Thirumurugan Gandhi|date=2018-08-10|work=The News Minute|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/2018/aug/10/thirumurugan-gandhi-held-in-bengaluru-for-un-speech-on-police-firing-in-thoothukudi-1855732.html|title=Thirumurugan Gandhi held in Bengaluru for UN speech on police firing in Thoothukudi|work=The New Indian Express|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref>\n* [[Indian National Congress]] party president [[Rahul Gandhi]] described it as \"[[state-sponsored terrorism]]\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://zeenews.india.com/india/anti-sterlite-protest-gunning-down-9-people-by-police-in-tamil-nadu-is-state-sponsored-terrorism-says-rahul-gandhi-2110523.html?src=fb|title=Anti-Sterlite protest: Gunning down 9 people by police in Tamil Nadu is state-sponsored terrorism, says Rahul Gandhi|date=2018-05-22|work=Zee News|access-date=2018-05-22|language=en}}</ref> \n*[[Seeman (politician)|Seeman]] condemned the firing, and his political party held a rally in Tirunelveli condemning the shooting.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tamil.oneindia.com/news/tamilnadu/seeman-condemns-the-gun-firing-at-thoothukudi-protest/articlecontent-pf308746-320470.html|title=Naam Thamizhar Katchi leader Seeman condemns gun firing at Thoothukudi|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=2018-05-31}}</ref>\n* [[Kamal Haasan]] was one of the first political leaders to arrive to Tuticorin to see the injured in the hospital, after the shootings.\n* [[Vaiko]] and [[M.K.Stalin]] demanded investigations into the shootings.<ref>http://indianexpress.com/article/india/mass-murder-of-innocent-people-dmks-stalin-questions-order-to-fire-at-anti-sterlite-protesters-5187874/</ref>\n* [[National Human Rights Commission of India]] demanded investigation into the killings.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2018/05/indian-police-accused-killing-11-protesters-180523134721427.html |title=Indian police accused of killing at least 11 protesters}}</ref> It asked its Director General (Investigation) to send a team headed by an [[Superintendent of Police|SP]] to visit the spot and conduct an inquiry.<ref name=\"TH20180530-1\" />\n* Tamils and [[Tamil diaspora]] across the world including [[United States]], [[Canada]], [[Europe]], [[Malaysia]], [[Sri Lanka]] and [[Australia]] held protests against the killing.\n* In support of the protests The UK's Opposition, Labour Party, has called for Vedanta to be delisted from the London Stock Exchange. [[John McDonnell]], the UK's Shadow Chancellor, said removing Vedanta Resources from the London financial markets would prevent reputational damage from the \"rogue\" company which has been operating \"illegal\" mining concerns for years. \"After the firing on the protestors this week, regulators must now take action. Vedanta must be immediately delisted from the London Stock Exchange to remove its cloak of respectability, restore confidence in the governance of the Stock Exchange, and prevent further reputational damage to London's financial markets from this rogue corporation,\" McDonnell said in a statement .<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/uk-opposition-wants-vedanta-delisted-from-london-stock-exchange/articleshow/64331300.cms |title=UK Opposition wants Vedanta delisted on London Stock Exchange}}</ref>\n* Actor [[Rajinikanth]] said \"anti-social elements had infiltrated the crowd causing violence and should have been dealt with an iron hand\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wionews.com/india-news/rajinikanth-issued-summons-over-anti-social-elements-remark-on-tuticorin-violence-firing-278579|title=Rajinikanth issued summons over \u2018anti-social elements\u2019 remark on Tuticorin violence, firing|website=WION|language=en|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref> and also stated that Tamil Nadu would become a graveyard if the people of the state keep protesting against everything<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-44313804|title=Rajinikanth: Anger after actor justifies deadly police firing|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/rajinikanth-blames-anti-social-elements-for-sterlite-protest201805302030500001/ |title=Rajinikanth blames anti-social elements for Sterlite protest}}</ref>. Also, his angry reaction on media was criticized and his statements were brought negative impact on social media.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-superstar-rajinikanth-apologises-for-losing-cool-at-media-interaction-2621031 |title=Superstar Rajinikanth apologises for losing cool at media interaction |access-date=3 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/rajinikanth-s-speech-earns-him-negative-image-on-social-media-news-tamil-sf5jD6fcigihb.html|title=Rajinikanth's speech earns him negative image on social media?|access-date=3 June 2018}}</ref> Following his controversial statements regarding the Thoothukudi shooting scandal, the Tamil activist groups in [[Norway]] and [[Switzerland]] banned the release of Rajinikanth's [[Kaala (2018 film)|''Kaala'']] in Norway and Switzerland by the scheduled world wide release date as of 7 June.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tamil.news18.com/news/entertainment/after-norway-kaala-ban-in-swiss-too-24491.html|title=\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bbe \u0baa\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0b9f \u0bae\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u2013 News18 Tamil|website=News18 Tamil|access-date=2018-06-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tamil.samayam.com/tamil-cinema/movie-news/rajinikanth-kaala-movie-banned-in-switzerland-and-norway/articleshow/64428551.cms|title=\u0bb0\u0b9c\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc7, \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bbe \u0baa\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc8 - Samayam Tamil|date=2018-06-02|work=[[Samayam Tamil]]|access-date=2018-06-03|language=ta}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/foreign-nations-ban-rajinis-kaala-tamil-news-214931|title=Foreign nations ban Rajini's 'Kaala'? - Tamil Movie News \u2013 IndiaGlitz.com|work=IndiaGlitz.com|access-date=2018-06-03}}</ref> The Tamil diaspora groups in Norway and Switzerland announced that they would not release the films of actors in the future who deliberately hurt the feelings and attitudes of Tamil people following the comments from Rajinikanth on Tamils.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tamilnews.com/2018/06/01/switzerland-ban-super-star-movie-following-norway/|title=\u0ba8\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0bb8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd '\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bbe' \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc8??|last=S|first=Ashwiniya|date=2018-06-01|work=TAMIL NEWS|access-date=2018-06-03|language=en-US}}</ref> However, the ban was later on lifted and the film was released with a week delay resp. a day before the scheduled worldwide release in Switzerland and Norway, respectively.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.topkino.ch/pdf/Programm24.pdf|title=Wochenprogramm|date=2018-06-11|work=Top Kino|access-date=2018-06-19|language=de-CH|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619085834/http://www.topkino.ch/pdf/Programm24.pdf|archivedate=2018-06-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.filmweb.no/film/article1361077.ece|title=Kaala (Tamil)|date=2018-06-01|work=Filmweb|access-date=2018-06-19|language=no-NO|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619090401/https://www.filmweb.no/film/article1361077.ece|archivedate=2018-06-19}}</ref>  The actor was also summoned to appear before the one man commission probing the incident on 25th February. However, the actor cited professional engagements and disturbance caused to the public if a star of his stature arrives at the court to decline appearing before the commission. He has since filed an affidavit with the commission answering the questions posed by them<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/south/thoothukudi-sterlite-copper-plant-probe-rajinikanth-gets-exemption-from-appearance-808094.html|title=Thoothukudi Sterlite Copper plant probe: Rajinikanth gets exemption from appearance|date=2020-02-25|website=Deccan Herald|language=en|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>.\n\nA video released by the environmental activist a few days before he went missing from a train while traveling to Madurai from Chennai, S. Mugilan says the \"shooting was well planned\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/rights/environmental-activist-missing-thoothukudi-massacre-police|title=Activist Goes Missing Hours After Incriminating Top Cops in Thoothukudi Massacre|website=The Wire|access-date=2019-03-20}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=TuNo|title=Arsonists - Sterlite - The Hidden Truth - \u0b95\u0bca\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd? \u0bb8\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b9f\u0bcd - \u0bae\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0b89\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd|date=2019-02-08|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SlukGKrzYLc|access-date=2019-03-20}}</ref>\n\n== Government response ==\nOn 28 May 2018, the Sterlite factory was sealed by an order of the Tamil Nadu Environmental pollutions and Forests Department.<ref name=\"TH20180528-1\">{{cite news | last = Rohit | first = T. K. | title = Sterlite Copper to be permanently closed, says Tamil Nadu government | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Chennai | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 28 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/sterlite-copper-to-be-permanently-closed-says-tamil-nadu-government/article24014605.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref> The next day, Tamil Nadu's State Industries Promotion Corporation (SIPCOT) announced that it would take back 342.22 acres of land that it had given for expansion of the facility.<ref name=\"TH20180530-1\">{{cite news | title = T.N. to take back land allotted to Sterlite | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Chennai / New Delhi | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 30 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/tn-to-take-back-land-allotted-to-sterlite/article24029865.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref> Many political leaders  including [[M.K.Stalin]], [[Seeman (politician)|Seeman]] and [[Anbumani Ramadoss]] criticised the sealing order, saying that it would not stand up to legal scrutiny since the government had given no reason for shutting down the factory<ref name=\"TH20180530-2\">{{cite news | title = G.O. won't stand up to legal scrutiny: Stalin | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Chennai | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 30 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/go-wont-stand-up-to-legal-scrutiny-stalin/article24027956.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"TH20180530-3\">{{cite news | title = G.O. to close Sterlite plant inadequate | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Chennai | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 30 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/go-to-close-sterlite-plant-inadequate/article24030059.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref>.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Manjolai Labourers massacre]]\n* [[2018 Tamil Nadu protests for Kaveri water sharing]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Pollution in India]]\n[[Category:Police brutality in India]]\n[[Category:2018 in Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:2018 murders in Asia]]\n[[Category:May 2018 crimes in Asia|Thoothukudi_firing]]\n[[Category:Thoothukudi]]\n[[Category:Protests in India]]\n", "name_user": "Aniruddha060", "label": "safe", "comment": "Removed template", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thoothukudi_massacre"}
