e news |last=McNeil, Jr. |first=Donald G. |title=The U.S. Now Leads the World in Confirmed Coronavirus Cases\u2014Following a series of missteps, the nation is now the epicenter of the pandemic. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/26/health/usa-coronavirus-cases.html |date=26 March 2020 |work=[[The New York Times]] |accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n}}\n<!-- ==Sources attribution== -->* {{Free-content attribution |title=290&nbsp;million students out of school due to COVID-19: UNESCO releases first global numbers and mobilizes response |publisher=UNESCO |documentURL= https://en.unesco.org/news/290-million-students-out-school-due-covid-19-unesco-releases-first-global-numbers-and-mobilizes |licence statement URL= https://en.unesco.org/news/290-million-students-out-school-due-covid-19-unesco-releases-first-global-numbers-and-mobilizes |licence=CC BY-SA 3.0 IGO|howto=no }}\n*{{Free-content attribution |title=Coronavirus impacts education |publisher=UNESCO |documentURL= https://en.unesco.org/themes/education-emergencies/coronavirus-school-closures |licence statement URL= https://en.unesco.org/themes/education-emergencies/coronavirus-school-closures |licence=CC BY-SA 3.0 IGO|howto=no }}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Sister project links|voy=2019\u20132020 coronavirus pandemic|c=category:COVID-19 pandemic|d=Q81068910|q=no|b=no|v=no|s=Category:COVID-19|m=no|mw=no|wikt=COVID-19|species=Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|n=Category:COVID-19}}\n{{Scholia}}\n\n'''Government health agencies'''\n*[https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019 COVID-19] ([http://www.who.int/news-room/q-a-detail/q-a-coronaviruses Questions & Answers]) by the [[World Health Organization]]\n*[https://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/novel-coronavirus-china COVID-19] ([http://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/novel-coronavirus-china/questions-answers Q&A]) by the [[European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control]]\n*[http://en.nhc.gov.cn/antivirusfight.html COVID-19] by the [[China National 